.TH "kvm_handle_wfx" 9 "kvm_handle_wfx" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
kvm_handle_wfx \- handle a wait-for-interrupts or wait-for-event instruction executed by a guest
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" kvm_handle_wfx
.BI "(struct kvm_vcpu *vcpu "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vcpu" 12
the vcpu pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
WFE: Yield the CPU and come back to this vcpu when the scheduler
decides to.
WFI: Simply call \fBkvm_vcpu_block\fP, which will halt execution of
world-switches and schedule other host processes until there is an
incoming IRQ or FIQ to the VM.
